The paper proposes a new abstract interpretation framework for static verification of interrupt-driven software, which is a topic that falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the interaction between interrupts and hardware, which is relevant to the computer architecture (cs.AR) sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on safety-critical systems, which is a topic that falls under the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the analysis of embedded systems, which is a topic that falls under the embedded systems (cs.EMBD) sub-category.
